 THE COMMUNIST BLOC\n\nUSSR: The Soviet Union has launched a major program to purchase large, modern tankers in the free world in order to reduce its dependence on chartered Western vessels. Negotiations with the Netherlands, Italy, and Japan have resulted in Soviet contracts for seven tankers, two of them already delivered, and negotiations are under way for at least 12 others, with tonnages ranging from 25,000 to 48,000 dead-weight tons each. The first tanker purchased under this program already is en route to the Black Sea to load petroleum for Cuba. All but two Soviet-owned tankers in operation heretofore have been in the 11,000-ton class or smaller", "token_count": 111, "token_end_0based": 118, "token_start_0based": 8, "token_text": "i the communist bloc ussr the soviet union has launched a major program to purchase large modern tankers in the free world in order to reduce its dependence on chartered western vessels negotiations with the netherlands italy and japan have resulted in soviet contracts for seven tankers two of them already delivered and negotiations are under way for at least 12 others with tonnages ranging from 25 000 to 48 000 dead-weight tons each the first tanker purchased under this program already is en route to the black sea to load petroleum for cuba all but two soviet-owned tankers in operation heretofore have been in the 11 000-ton class or smaller", "unred_source_page": 4}
